item.title: Rblogdown Setup
item.description: Alright I finally was able to setup Rblogdown with something resembling a type that I wanted. The biggest problem I had was the inability to figure out a decent workflow of things. That’s the main way to get these things to all talk together. Here’s a helpful video tutorial of the setup. My biggest issue I had was with Hugo. They have a bunch of different themes but I didn’t like very many of them and I have no html, css, javascript or bootstrap experience.

item.title: Emission Trading System Outlook
item.description: ​ What is the most effective policy measures for preventing climate change? This singular question has been in the back of leaders' minds ever since the first national UNFCC in 1992. By December 1997, in Kyoto, Japan, the market mechanism of cap-and-trade systems was conceived as the new pathway for reducing greenhouse gas emissions proposed by the United States. Since then, more national and subnational jurisdictions and private sector entities are adopting carbon pricing.
